Housing Price Prediction üè°
Project Overview:
This project aims to predict housing prices using machine learning techniques, focusing on providing accurate and reliable predictions. The Decision Tree algorithm emerged as the best-performing model among the tested algorithms.

Algorithms Used:

Linear Regression
Random Forest
Decision Tree (Best Performing)
Features:

Data exploration with Pandas and NumPy
Data preprocessing for optimal performance
Feature scaling and selection using Min-Max scaling and scikit-learn
Implementation of Linear Regression, Random Forest, and Decision Tree models
Technologies:

Python
scikit-learn
Pandas
NumPy
Matplotlib
Seaborn
Goals:

Predict housing prices with high accuracy
Analyze the impact of different regression algorithms
Provide a reliable model for real estate trends
Methodology:

Data Exploration: Conducted an in-depth analysis using Pandas and NumPy.
Preprocessing: Cleaned and transformed data for optimal model performance.
Feature Scaling and Selection: Applied Min-Max scaling and used scikit-learn's SelectFromModel for feature selection.
Regression Models: Implemented and evaluated Linear Regression, Random Forest, and Decision Tree models.
